==English==
===Noun===
'''skank'''
#Any [[substance]] considered particularly [[foul]] or [[unpleasant]]
#A [[promiscuous]] [[woman]]
#A [[dance]] popular in [[California]]'s [[hardcore]] [[punk]] [[scene]] in the 1980's.  The [[mascot]] of the [[Circle Jerks]], [[Skankman]], was typically portrayed going through its [[motion]]s.  
===Etymology===
Middle English (combination of the words scold and brank): The word [[brank]], a word of British origin referring to frolicsome and often lascivious conduct, is combined with the word ''scold'' to  describe a woman who is condemned for her promiscious behavior. 
